<p>Via <a href="https://twitter.com/objcio">objc.io</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/mxcl">Max Howell's</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/mxcl/status/1065802821700857856">retweet</a>, TIL about Swift's inline computed properties. Another one to try on Org <a href="https://orgmode.org/worg/org-contrib/babel/intro.html">Babel</a>. ‚Äè</p>
<pre><code class="language-swift">func greetWorld() {
 var message = &quot;hello&quot;
 var betterMessage: String {
   return &quot;\(message) world&quot;
 }
 print(betterMessage)
}

greetWorld()
</code></pre>
